"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131679","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-06-19","<p>The funding agreement includes the following:</p><p>• Consult with local Westminster community groups, including housing associations, over 50’s, Mother and Toddler groups, schools, about the proposed Holocaust Memorial.</p><p>• Encourage people to write to Westminster City Council with their views.</p><p>• Produce short social media videos on the Holocaust Memorial <br> <br>• Support UK Holocaust Memorial Foundation and the Department on publicity and campaigns around the time Time Capsule<br> <br> • Create an engagement campaign<br> <br> • Organise community engagement activity.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-06-19T14:43:15.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131679/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131679/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-06-12","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 29 May to Question 256928, if he will place in the Library the parts of the Government’s agreement with Big Ideas relating to the Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre which set out the work to be done by Big Ideas.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","263698"
