"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131391","Home Office","false","2019-06-19","<p>The Home Office closed the Campsfield House Immigration Removal Centre in Kidlington, Oxfordshire on 31 May 2019.</p><p><br>When disposing of surplus property assets the Home Office will always seek best value for the taxpayer.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-06-19T12:01:33.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131391/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131391/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-06-11","Home Office: Empty Property","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will publish the names and locations of the land and buildings owned by his Department that are (a) sitting empty and (b) in the process of being sold or disposed of; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","263039"
